text:
That controller issue is because she just plugged the controller in and jumped right into the game. To use a Dualshock you need to set it up first using the DS4Windows program, or nowadays setting up controllers in Steam itself works too. I much prefer DS4Windows personally.

Microsoft were a bunch of maroons after they tried to make their own controller and realised that swapping the buttons and the analogue stick directions around was one way to avoid a lawsuit for copying the controller patent.

It's a simple fix, but Gura should first fix that and have a look at a picture of the xbox controller to get familiar with the button prompts. Or just freaking buy an xbox controller like how much money does she get to not even have this stuff already XD
